+ Install the plug-in:
  unzip org.eventb.eventBKeyboard.zip -d $eclipse
     where $eclipse the directory of your installed Eclipse
     
+ Install Brave Sans Mono font:
  The Text Area uses Brave Sans Mono font which is include in the ./fonts directory
  You need to install the font first before running eclipse (?)
  You can either install system-wide or just user-specific

  - System-wide (need root access)
	mkdir /usr/share/fonts/ttf
	cp $eclipse/plugins/org.eventb.eventBKeyboard_2.0.0/fonts/*.ttf /usr/share/fonts/ttf/
	cd /usr/share/fonts/ttf
	ttmkfdir > fonts.scale
	mkfontdir

	/usr/sbin/chkfontpath -a /usr/share/fonts/ttf

	to check
	/usr/sbin/chkfontpath

	....
	30: /usr/share/fonts/ttf
  
  - User-specific (Make sure that your home directory can be read by others :-) )
    mkdir ~/.fonts
    cp $eclipse/plugins/org.eventb.eventBKeyboard_1.0.0/fonts/*.ttf ~/.fonts
    cd ~/.fonts
    mkfontdir
    mkfontscale
    xset fp rehash
    

Happy typing !!!
